snippet.textDisplay: Britain's Pretend Democracy : Regrettably a tiny number of billionaires like Lord Rothermere, Richard Desmond, Rupert Murdoch and the Barclay brothers control much of the British news media. Multi-millionaires also often present, write and edit much of our news media. In reality these elite are the gatekeepers to our democracy and they ALWAYS get their man. Those who insist "well Blair got abuse and won elections" are wilfully ignoring reality. In 1995 Tony Blair flew halfway around the world to meet with Murdoch's News Corporation on Hayman Island and effectively secure their support or get permission to win - depending on how you see it. In 1997, Britain's biggest selling daily newspaper and Murdoch rag threw it's full support behind Tony Blair with the front page headline "The Sun Backs Blair". Indeed the Sun has backed the winner and aggressively attacked the eventual loser of every single British General Election since Thatcher. Whilst the overwhelming majority of these winning candidates are Conservative, it's useful for billionaires to let the occasional (conservative) Labour leader win eventually, to help create the illusion for the people that they have a genuine democratic choice. The last thing the billionaire moguls want, is for ordinary people to wake up to the blatant fact that the rich are completely in charge. That they shout "Jump!" and we repeatedly ask "How high?"....The battle of the 21st century is exactly the same as the battle of the 20th century. It's utterly tragic to see we have not moved on. The Wallet Vs The Ballot .. and the wallet has consistently won over decades. ... This is the reality of Britain's Pretend Democracy.

snippet.textDisplay:
I know very few people want to hear this but - this is my opinion;

JC was always opposed to the EU in purely ideological terms - because he is a pure, unadulterated, unreconstructed, Social Democrat - and the EU has neoliberalism baked into its heart - which he cannot tollerate - as he is neoliberal intollerant...

BUT - above that, more significant to him, than that - he is a democrat - AND leader of a party that is massively in favour of staying inside the EU - two things, that are totally mutually exclusive and that is just the start- next;

Even though he is ideologically opposed to the EU, he has been forced to recognise that; leaving the EU - is bad for people, real people - you cannot point to a single, fact checked, bonafide report that shows the population of the UK being better-off post Brexit - yet, in their millions, the turkies, who are the population of dozens of Labour supporting constituencies around the country - are cueing up to be stunned, bled, gutted and trussed, thence to be served up on the dinner tables of the people who will actually benefit from Brexit.

Do you see - there is no upside for anyone in this process who actually cares about the outcome - the only people still rooting for Brexit, other than the turkies, are the billionaires, who fund the Tory party, and make money from chaos.

Corbyn could not win, the people will not win...
R.I.P Labour, you will never reclaim the North
